1.00	D%C3%ADa_Especial	Día Especial	"Día Especial" (English: ) is a Latin pop ballad performed by Colombian-born singer Shakira from her album Fijación Oral Vol. 1. The song is about how a day is made special from forgiveness. "Día Especial" is not an official single to Fijación Oral Vol. 1, but was popular around the time of the album's release, peaking at #26 on the US Billboard Latin Pop Songs. Gustavo Cerati was the lyricist for the track with Shakira and Luis Fernando Ochoa as co-writers for the music. The English version is entitled "The Day and the Time" and features on the album Oral Fixation Vol. 2.	
